hopobject.body: Have you read any good books lately? ambi climate price If she's successful, Earhart won't be the first woman to re-create Amelia Earhart's final flight, says Louise Foudray, 84, caretaker and historian at the Amelia Earhart Birthplace Museum in Atchison, Kan. For instance, Foudray mentions Anne Pellegreno who completed the planned flight July 7, 1967, in a Lockheed 10A Electra, and Gaby Kennard, an Australian, who did it in 1989 in a Piper Saratoga.
